@startuml
!pragma svgparser sax
' Regression test: two SVG sprites each containing polygon elements in the same diagram.
' Previously caused a Width/Height = Integer.MAX_VALUE crash when polygon points used
' space-separated coordinates (valid per SVG spec) rather than comma-separated pairs.
' See: polygon points="x,y x,y" vs "x y x y" — both must be supported.

sprite hexagon <svg viewBox="0 0 60 60" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
  <polygon points="30,5 55,17.5 55,42.5 30,55 5,42.5 5,17.5" fill="#4285f4" stroke="#1a73e8" stroke-width="2"/>
</svg>

sprite diamond <svg viewBox="0 0 60 60" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
  <polygon points="30,5 55,30 30,55 5,30" fill="#34a853" stroke="#1e8e3e" stroke-width="2"/>
</svg>

Alice -> Bob : Hexagon shape <$hexagon>
Bob -> Alice : Diamond shape <$diamond>

note right of Bob
  Multi-polygon sprite test:
  <$hexagon> hexagon
  <$diamond> diamond
end note
@enduml
